columns.name: subnet_id
columns.description: Contains the unique ID to specify a subnet.

columns.name: subnet_arn
columns.description: Contains the Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the subnet.

columns.name: vpc_id
columns.description: ID of the VPC, the subnet is in.

columns.name: cidr_block
columns.description: Contains the IPv4 CIDR block assigned to the subnet.

columns.name: owner_id
columns.description: Contains the AWS account that own the subnet.

columns.name: assign_ipv6_address_on_creation
columns.description: Indicates whether a network interface created in this subnet (including a network interface created by RunInstances) receives an IPv6 address.

columns.name: available_ip_address_count
columns.description: The number of unused private IPv4 addresses in the subnet. The IPv4 addresses for any stopped instances are considered unavailable.

columns.name: availability_zone
columns.description: The Availability Zone of the subnet.

columns.name: availability_zone_id
columns.description: The AZ ID of the subnet.

columns.name: customer_owned_ipv4_pool
columns.description: The customer-owned IPv4 address pool associated with the subnet.

columns.name: default_for_az
columns.description: Indicates whether this is the default subnet for the Availability Zone.

columns.name: map_customer_owned_ip_on_launch
columns.description: Indicates whether a network interface created in this subnet (including a network interface created by RunInstances) receives a customer-owned IPv4 address.

columns.name: map_public_ip_on_launch
columns.description: Indicates whether instances launched in this subnet receive a public IPv4 address.

columns.name: outpost_arn
columns.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the Outpost. Available only if subnet is on an outpost.

columns.name: ipv6_cidr_block_association_set
columns.description: A list of IPv6 CIDR blocks associated with the subnet.

columns.name: tags_src
columns.description: A list of tags that are attached to the subnet.
